This paper deals with image restoration, which is a common problem in computer vision. The proposed method involves iterative denoising and backward projections, which are techniques commonly used in signal processing and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also provides theoretical analysis and compares the proposed method with existing techniques, which suggests that it may also be relevant to other sub-categories such as cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
